            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">4. Young 32 years pure vegetarian, busy businessman, with history of frequently skipping of meals due to his daily busy work schedule. He presented with history of fatigue, occasional dyspnoea on exertion and climbing stairs with weight loss of 2 kg in 3 months, he has no history of fever or bleeding from any site. on examination he has pallor and mild icterus, Rest of examination is essentially normal. His blood workup showed Hb 7gm%, MCV 130fl,Total WBC-3700/cumm,Platelet is 100,000/cumm. Peripheral smears showed hyper segmented neutrophil and macro ovalocytes what is the most  likely diagnosis is?</p>"
