                  "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20 black\">Correct!</p><p>Correct answer is C : HPV 23, 24<br/>Gardasil, the new vaccine against human papilloma virus (HPV) âHPV, which causes cervical cancer and genital warts <br />\nHere is what you need to know now about this new vaccine.<br />\n1. What is Gardasil?<br />\nGardasil is a vaccine, licensed for use in June 2006, by the FDA. It targets four strains of human papillomavirus (HPV) -- HPV-6, 11, 16, and 18. HPV-16 and HPV-18 account for about 70% of all cervical cancers. HPV-6 and -11 cause about 90% of genital warts. HPV is also linked to anal cancer..</p>"
